{
  "text": "We begin by recalling that M has cohomology concentrated in even degrees. Indeed, by base change, the stalk of M at a point x \u2208 O \u00b5 is (an even shift of) the cohomology of the fiber \u03c0 \u22121 (x). By [CITATION_1] Theorem 2.5 ], \u03c0 \u22121 (x) has an affine paving, so",
